I LOVE that we have so many cool adventure opportunities on this planet, and I want YOU to join me and #crushit4climate this month! This is a fun reminder to enjoy our amazing outdoors while learning what we can do to keep them clean. 
🤩
Here’s the deal - every week in my bio I’ll be linking an article relating to climate change. Read the article, follow @protectourwinters and join their email list on protectourwinters.org to learn how you can get involved. Then get outside on a rad adventure and if you post about it, tag me - I want to see what you did!

To keep you inspired, each week I’ve got some really sick giveaways from @llbean, @oakleyskiing, @nuunhydration & @swixsportus. node.text:
I love a good epic run in the mountains! I love skiing beautiful trails. I love breathing clean air, and I want to share this love of adventuring outdoors with everyone around me...and generations to come. And I think many of you do, too! So I have an ask of you that will take 5 minutes of your day to make an impact. 

It occurred to me, training in the ski hall in Oberhof, that the way we’re currently going this could someday be the only way to experience skiing…which would be heartbreaking. 

We all want to take the little steps we can in our own lives, but one bigger step to take as a country is updating the electric grid. Our current grid is out of date, and updating to move us away from fossil fuels and towards clean and reliable energy can also create jobs and protect our world from extreme weather. Right now, Congress is writing the final text of the second part of the infrastructure package…which is where all of us come in. We are relying on the budget reconciliation bill to include the critical climate funding we need to move in the right direction in this climate crisis. We all have a voice, and this is a good time to use it!

Please ask your lawmakers to include critical funding to support updating our electric grid so we can #buildbackcleaner @mittromney @moniquelimonca @kyrstensinema @johnhickenlooper @senatorjontester @stevedaines 

Follow the link in my bio to email your Senator and learn more through @protectourwinters 

(Last 📷 by @bllharmeyer1)

node.text:
As promised…sharing more of the recipes I’m using during training to help me recover quickly and stay on top of my energy needs! 💪🏼 After intervals, I want to immediately give my body the quick-digesting carbs, BCAA’s for muscle repair and electrolytes it needs, even before I begin the cool down phase of the workout. So I’ve been making homemade “shot blocks” with @nuunhydration recovery mix (pick your flavor, I like blackberry lemon) and honey! Eating your hydration? Yup! 

I also love that this helps me cut down on single-use plastics, since I can make one big pan of blocks and carry a few with me at a time during training in mini tupperware containers! The gelatin gives me an extra collagen boost which doesn’t hurt, either.

The recipe: 
-2 cups of Nuun Recovery (1 scoop mixed into 2 cups water)
-2 T honey
-2 packets Knox unflavored gelatin powder

Sprinkle the gelatin over 1/2 cup of Nuun in a bowl. Heat the rest of the Nuun and honey until just boiling, then pour over the cold Nuun and gelatin, whisk until combined, pour into pan and let set in the fridge for a few hours. Cut into squares, put into mini containers and go training! 

P.S. Don’t be scared of the sugars and protein, or fueling before, during and after a workout…your body needs the energy, and it helps you lock in all the hard work you just did! #nuunathlete #nuunlife

From fog and 100% humidity to clouds to a sunny ridge. The many faces and stages of a long run in the Whites! ☺️🤨🤩😵‍💫🤪
I also get a lot of asks for what makes a “long run” long, and for me these days, it’s anything over 3 hours. It’s not about the miles covered, just the time out on my feet. But more than the time, it’s about the way I feel when I’m out training - gotta appreciate all the little moments and the things that make it fun! #TimeToPlay #RunOnEmotion @salomonrunning

Wow, that was cool! For my 30th birthday coming up, Wade took me to stay a night in one of the huts in the White Mountains of New Hampshire - the Galehead hut, for those of you who know it! 
And for those of you who know ME, you’ll know that every summer I usually pick a crazy long distance adventure titled “the big stupid”. This year I decided to be smart for once (I know, I was also shocked) and forgo the risk of injury…but I still got my sense of adventure in with a night up in the mountains and an epic ridge run the next day before hiking back out! 
My heart is so happy. I can’t recommend it enough. And a big thank you to @llbean for all the hiking gear! 😍 #beanoutsider #llbeanambassador
